This PR brings the test module into PEP8 compliance and makes
use of the Unittest's native asserts.
This requires a yet-to-be-released version of dlib (probably will be 19.5). So it can't be merged yet.

Hi, I Added face recognition with a k-nearest neighbors classifier.
The classifier is trained on a set of known people, and can recognize people based on training set.
The k-nearest neighbors approach where distance is calculated in the face-encoding space should work well for large sets of known people. It uses sklearn's KNN classifier with a ball-tree implementation.
Also added option for visualization of the results.

After several hours trying to run face_recognition on the GPU, I created this Dockerfile with Dlib installed + CUDA and cuDNN. Ready to use on the GPU with Nvidia-Docker.
It can dramatically reduce the number of issues regarding the usage on the GPU.
Full example: https://github.com/enric1994/face_recognition_docker_gpu

Use of exit or quit method will raise error if interpreter is started with -S flag.
The exit and quit functions are actually site.Quitter objects and are loaded, at interpreter start up, from site.py. However, if the interpreter is started with the -S flag, or a custom site.py is used then exit and quit may not be present. It is recommended to use sys.exit() which is built into the interpreter and is guaranteed to be present.
